{% comment %}
  snippets/product-popup.liquid
  ------------------------------------------------------------------
  Per-product popup panel. Rendered once per Grid tile, INSIDE that
  tile's own .product-grid__image-wrap, from
  sections/product-grid.liquid:
    {% render 'product-popup', product: grid_product %}

  ARCHITECTURE NOTE (image-anchored, not a viewport modal):
  This is deliberately NOT a fixed full-screen modal with a backdrop.
  Each popup is a direct child of its own product's image wrapper —
  the same positioning container the tile's "+" hotspot lives in —
  and is positioned with `position: absolute` relative to that
  wrapper (see gift-guide.css). It opens attached to the image it
  belongs to, not centered over the whole viewport, and it is never
  appended to <body>. There is no shared/global popup: every tile
  renders its own independent instance, scoped to its own product id.

  Hidden by default (the `hidden` attribute below); opened by its own
  tile's circular marker via data-popup-target="popup-{{ product.id }}",
  wired in assets/gift-guide.js → initPopups(). Close happens on the
  "X" button, on an outside click, or Escape — all scoped to this
  instance, never affecting another product's popup.

  Layout confirmed against Figma reference screenshots: photo is
  small/square and sits BESIDE name/price/description (not stacked
  full-width above them) — see .product-popup__top below. Field
  order: close (X, top-right) → [photo | name/price/description] row
  → Color (two-way segmented toggle) → Size (custom dropdown, not a
  native <select> — see .product-popup__size-dropdown) → Add to Cart.

  Size dropdown uses a native <details>/<summary> element rather than
  <select> so it can show its options as an in-place expanding list
  (matching the reference) with zero JS required just to open/close —
  the browser handles that natively. Each option is still tagged with
  data-option-name/data-option-value so Phase 4's initVariantPickers()
  can wire click-to-select the same way it already will for the Color
  toggle; it should also update the summary's visible text and close
  the <details> on selection.

  Depends on:
    - assets/gift-guide.css → panel/toggle/dropdown styling, plus the
      absolute-positioning rule that anchors this popup to its parent
      .product-grid__image-wrap (popup can't use a {% style %} tag —
      that tag is section/block-only, not available in snippets — so
      all of this snippet's CSS lives in the shared stylesheet
      instead).
    - assets/gift-guide.js → initPopups() (open/close, scoped per
      instance) and initVariantPickers()/addToCart() (Phase 4 — still
      needs to wire selection state + summary text update for the new
      dropdown).
{% endcomment %}

{%- if product != blank -%}
  <div
    class="product-popup"
    id="popup-{{ product.id }}"
    data-product-popup
    data-product-id="{{ product.id }}"
    role="dialog"
    aria-labelledby="PopupTitle-{{ product.id }}"
    hidden
  >
    <div class="product-popup__panel">
      <button type="button" class="product-popup__close" data-popup-close aria-label="Close">
        &times;
      </button>

      {%- comment %} Photo + name/price/description sit side by side — confirmed against the Figma reference, not stacked. {% endcomment -%}
      <div class="product-popup__top">
        {%- if product.featured_image != blank -%}
          <img
            src="{{ product.featured_image | image_url: width: 300 }}"
            alt="{{ product.featured_image.alt | default: product.title | escape }}"
            loading="lazy"
            width="300"
            height="{{ 300 | divided_by: product.featured_image.aspect_ratio }}"
            class="product-popup__image"
          >
        {%- endif -%}

        <div class="product-popup__info">
          <h3 id="PopupTitle-{{ product.id }}" class="product-popup__title">{{ product.title }}</h3>

          {%- comment %} Same EUR/comma-decimal/€-suffix note as product-grid.liquid — depends on Settings → General → currency formatting. {% endcomment -%}
          <p class="product-popup__price">{{ product.price | money }}</p>

          <p class="product-popup__description">{{ product.description | strip_html | truncate: 200 }}</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      {%- comment %}
        Same options_with_values-driven pattern as before — nothing
        hardcoded, so this works for any product's real option values
        (e.g. the seeded catalog's XS/S/M/L, not the Figma mock's
        XS–XL/6XL example state — see build-context doc §4a's callout
        on this).
      {%- endcomment -%}
      <div class="product-popup__variant-picker" data-variant-picker>
        {%- assign popup_color_option = product.options_with_values | where: "name", "Color" | first -%}
        {%- if popup_color_option -%}
          <p class="product-popup__label">Color</p>
          <div class="product-popup__colors" role="group" aria-label="Color">
            {%- for value in popup_color_option.values -%}
              <button
                type="button"
                class="product-popup__color-swatch"
                data-option-name="Color"
                data-option-value="{{ value | escape }}"
                aria-pressed="{% if forloop.first %}true{% else %}false{% endif %}"
              >
                {{ value }}
              </button>
            {%- endfor -%}
          </div>
        {%- endif -%}

        {%- assign popup_size_option = product.options_with_values | where: "name", "Size" | first -%}
        {%- if popup_size_option -%}
          <p class="product-popup__label">Size</p>
          {%- comment %} Native disclosure widget: opens/closes with no JS. Phase 4 wires the actual selection (click an <li>, copy its text into the <summary>, set data-option-value on the wrapper, close the details). {% endcomment -%}
          <details class="product-popup__size-dropdown" data-option-name="Size">
            <summary class="product-popup__size-summary">
              <span data-size-summary-text>Choose your size</span>
              <span class="product-popup__chevron" aria-hidden="true"></span>
            </summary>
            <ul class="product-popup__size-options">
              {%- for value in popup_size_option.values -%}
                <li>
                  <button type="button" class="product-popup__size-option" data-option-name="Size" data-option-value="{{ value | escape }}">
                    {{ value }}
                  </button>
                </li>
              {%- endfor -%}
            </ul>
          </details>
        {%- endif -%}
      </div>

      <button type="button" class="product-popup__add-to-cart" data-add-to-cart disabled>
        ADD TO CART &rarr;
      </button>

      {%- comment %}
        Same [data-product-json] pattern as the grid tile's own copy.
        Both carry the same product id but live in different
        containers (this panel vs. the tile), so Phase 4's JS always
        scopes its lookup to the nearest ancestor with
        [data-product-id] rather than doing a bare global attribute
        match — the two never collide.
      {%- endcomment -%}
      <script type="application/json" data-product-json="{{ product.id }}">
        {{ product.variants | json }}
      </script>
    </div>
  </div>
{%- endif -%}